The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, August 05, 2004 				 Avaya takes charge of Tata Telecom
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 																								Mumbai, Aug. 4: Avaya Inc today took control of Tata Telecom  a provider of communication solutions for companies  by revamping its board of directors and renaming the company as Avaya GlobalConnect Limited.																								The new board will comprise eight distinguished business professionals with Mark Leigh as the new chairman. Tata Teleservices MD S. Ramakrishnan and National Securities Depository chief C. B. Bhave are on board.																								The move marked the completion of the deal between the Tatas and Avaya. 																								India is fast becoming a force to reckon with in the global market. Over the years, the company has recorded a 26 per cent growth and will continue to maintain a pace of 22-25 per cent in future, Leigh, who is also the president of Avaya in Asia-Pacific, said.																								I am confident that Avaya GlobalConnect and Avaya will deliver superior value to all stakeholders, he added. 																								Company vice-chairman Niru Mehta said Tata Telecom would continue to leverage its strengths and focus on customer responsiveness for consolidation of its leadership position in chosen markets. 																								In addition, we remain focused on exploring future growth opportunities by leveraging on our capabilities and further strengthening our end-to-end offerings, he added. 
